        <div id="mb1">
          <h2>Guan Yu Major Battles</h2>
            <div class="1">
                <li><b>180AD</b> - Guan Yu took part in the yellow turban Rebellion alongside Liu Bei and Zhang Fei as part of the volunteer malitia</li><br>
                <li><b>200AD</b> - He continued to work under Liu Bei, however Aafter being defeated by Cao Cao they wre split up. Liu Bei fled to Yuan Shao and Guan Yu captured.</li><br>
                <li><b>200AD</b> - After serving under Cao Cao for some time, Guan Yu received a number of gifts from Cao Cao and he could sense that Gaun wanted to leave and return to Liu Bei. When Guan Yu finally decided to leave, Cao Cao stopped his men
                    from pursuing him out of respect for his character.</li><br>
            </div>
            <div class="2">
                <li><b>208AD</b> - The battle of Guan Du gave both Liu Bei and Guan Yu a good chance to escape their current situation as Cao Cao attacked Yuan Shao. Both Liu Bei and Guan Yu fled south an d served under Liu Biao</li><br>
                <li><b>208AD</b> - Over the next two decades Liu Bei, Zhang Fei and Guan yu would take part in many military campaigns. After Liu Biaos death, Liu Bei began to make a base for himself by allying with the kingdom of Wu and Sun Quan. Their combined
                    efforts managed to keep Cao Cao from taking the whole of China and eventually lead to the forming of the Three Kingdoms.</li><br>
            </div>
            <div class="3">
                <li><b>219AD</b> - After gaining a substantial amount of land, the Shu Kingdom was formed and Guan Yu was given charge of the Jing Province. Guan Yu decided to launch an attack on Cao Cao, howver at this time relations between Shu and Wu had weakened. Sun sent a letter to Cao proposing a joint attack on Guan Yu and both sides know that Guan Yu would be a big problem that would have to be dealt with at some point. Once Guan launched the attack, Lu Meng of Wu came in and attacked from the rear. As Lu Meng attacked he also took Jiang Ling from Guan whch housed many of Guans officers families in. Lu Meng made a point to treat them properly and cause them no harm as to rattle the morale in Guans camp. Men slowly started to desert him as the pressure from both fronts increased however Guan refused to surrender. Guan tried to escape further however eventually himself and his son Guan Ping were captured and executed.</li><br>
            </div>
            <div class="4">
              <li>Guan Yu's name today represents the pinnacle of loyalty, bravery and strength. He has now became a legendary figure and considered a God. He is also a revered figure in Buddhism Confucianism and Chinese folk religion</li><br>
              <q><strong>I shall be allowed to set off to rejoin Uncle Liu Bei so soon as I shall hear where he is, whether it be far or near. </strong><cite>Guan Yu said to Cao Cao after surrendering to Cao Cao</cite></q><br>
            </div>
